747
00:40:54,291 --> 00:40:56,958
We've spent ten years
trying to reason with these pigs.

748
00:40:57,041 --> 00:40:58,833
That's enough. It's over.

749
00:40:58,916 --> 00:41:01,958
The Brotherhood was created
to fight for dignity.

750
00:41:02,833 --> 00:41:06,208
It seems like everything we've ever done
is being destroyed by these motherfuckers.

751
00:41:06,291 --> 00:41:07,416
We demand respect.

752
00:41:07,500 --> 00:41:09,375
Now it's time
to start fighting back, hard.

753
00:41:09,458 --> 00:41:12,458
Or watch in silence while
everything we've built gets demolished.

754
00:41:12,541 --> 00:41:14,583
They gotta understand
that we're in charge.

755
00:41:14,666 --> 00:41:15,916
Damn straight.

756
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,416
Either they agree to give up
on this transfer crap

757
00:41:18,500 --> 00:41:20,250
or we fuck shit up on a massive scale.

758
00:41:20,333 --> 00:41:22,875
Bro, here's the thing.
We're taking over the whole prison system.

759
00:41:22,958 --> 00:41:26,458
All at once, in one move.
That will teach them some respect.

760
00:41:26,541 --> 00:41:29,708
But commandeering the prisons
won't work. Not anymore.

761
00:41:29,791 --> 00:41:32,166
No one cares about what happens in there.

762
00:41:32,750 --> 00:41:33,708
The game's changed.

763
00:41:33,791 --> 00:41:35,958
We could burn
all the mattresses in Brazil,

764
00:41:36,041 --> 00:41:37,541
and no one would give a shit.

765
00:41:37,625 --> 00:41:41,375
He's right, goddammit.
Prison revolts won't do a thing anymore.

766
00:41:41,458 --> 00:41:45,000
They're treating us like shit,
so let's make sure we hit the fan.

767
00:41:45,500 --> 00:41:49,166
We change our strategy, and attack them
where it hurts the most, outside.

768
00:41:49,250 --> 00:41:52,541
-The game is on the streets now.
-Send them all to their graves.

769
00:41:52,625 --> 00:41:55,125
Any pig on the streets is shot,
no questions asked, bro.

770
00:41:55,208 --> 00:41:57,291
Wait, Ivan. Calm down, Calm down.

771
00:41:57,375 --> 00:41:59,666
The Brotherhood doesn't work
like that anymore.

772
00:41:59,750 --> 00:42:03,291
Please. It took years to prove
we could run without violence.

773
00:42:03,791 --> 00:42:05,875
And everyone sees
that we're making more money

774
00:42:05,958 --> 00:42:08,000
and helping our brothers in prison.

775
00:42:08,083 --> 00:42:10,291
I'm negotiating
with the Department of Security.

776
00:42:10,833 --> 00:42:13,958
-I just need more time, dammit.
-With all due respect, Counselor…

777
00:42:14,458 --> 00:42:17,250
they kidnap your niece
and this is how you react?

778
00:42:17,333 --> 00:42:19,166
Are you playing us for fools? Huh?

779
00:42:19,750 --> 00:42:22,333
Precisely. Precisely, Minor.

780
00:42:22,416 --> 00:42:26,541
The police have my brother's daughter,
who I raised as my very own.

781
00:42:26,625 --> 00:42:30,416
And yet, somehow, I don't think
killing is gonna solve anything.

782
00:42:30,500 --> 00:42:33,250
What about the brothers going
to solitary? What are we gonna do?

783
00:42:33,833 --> 00:42:36,375
Handle it peacefully, through legal means.

784
00:42:36,875 --> 00:42:39,541
I'll overturn the transfer in court
like I've always done.

785
00:42:39,625 --> 00:42:41,500
For all 500 of them, Counselor?

786
00:42:44,375 --> 00:42:46,458
Honestly, ma'am,
don't take this the wrong way,

787
00:42:46,541 --> 00:42:48,125
but go take care of your family.

788
00:42:48,208 --> 00:42:49,625
Show some respect, Gil.

789
00:42:50,125 --> 00:42:51,250
Respect. Got it?

790
00:42:54,333 --> 00:42:55,583
Ah, fuck!

791
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,166
We're fucked, Ivan.

792
00:43:02,875 --> 00:43:04,208
First block's started.

793
00:43:05,125 --> 00:43:08,333
Listen, here's the deal. They're starting
to move block one already.

794
00:43:08,416 --> 00:43:11,083
-Fuck.
-I'm giving you just one order.

795
00:43:11,166 --> 00:43:13,750
We take over the jails,
then we attack in the streets.

796
00:43:14,250 --> 00:43:16,916
It's over, man.
It's about time we sent them a message.

797
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:19,625
He's right.
They gotta learn to respect us.

798
00:43:19,708 --> 00:43:22,875
We're about to take down São Paulo.
The Brotherhood's going down in history.

799
00:43:22,958 --> 00:43:24,625
-This is war.
-We're the Brotherhood.

800
00:43:24,708 --> 00:43:25,791
Let's go!

801
00:43:25,875 --> 00:43:27,791
Come on!

802
00:43:27,875 --> 00:43:29,375
-Get up. Get up.
-Ivan.

803
00:43:29,458 --> 00:43:32,250
-Time to go for a stroll.
-Ivan, are you there?

804
00:43:32,333 --> 00:43:34,291
They're coming. It's going down.

805
00:43:34,375 --> 00:43:37,000
Make some coffee. Get up.

806
00:43:37,083 --> 00:43:38,500
-Ivan.
-Let's go!

807
00:43:38,583 --> 00:43:40,375
Who's callin' the shots
when you're not here?

808
00:43:41,875 --> 00:43:45,000
Time to pack. Time to get up.

809
00:43:45,083 --> 00:43:47,625
While I'm out of the picture,
command goes to Minor.

810
00:43:50,666 --> 00:43:52,458
Get up. Let's go. Come on.

811
00:43:54,333 --> 00:43:55,916
Time to go for a ride.

812
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:58,291
Come on, punk. Your taxi is here.

813
00:43:58,375 --> 00:43:59,708
Let me just get my stuff.

814
00:43:59,791 --> 00:44:02,500
You're not taking anything.
Your stuff will come later.

815
00:44:04,458 --> 00:44:06,041
Let's go, scumbag.

816
00:44:06,125 --> 00:44:08,250
Come on. Get up.

817
00:44:08,333 --> 00:44:10,041
-Get up! Get up!
-Go, go, go!

818
00:44:10,125 --> 00:44:11,833
You're going for a little stroll.

819
00:44:11,916 --> 00:44:14,166
Hey. I'm talking to you.
Get up. Let's go. Let's go.

820
00:44:14,250 --> 00:44:16,791
-Move, move, move!
-Let's go! Move, move, move!

821
00:44:34,250 --> 00:44:35,708
You heard him, dammit.

822
00:44:36,375 --> 00:44:37,666
Send the order out.

823
00:44:38,666 --> 00:44:40,250
-It's time!
-Yo, bro.

824
00:44:40,333 --> 00:44:43,250
-That's right. It's going down.
-The whole system is going down.

825
00:44:43,333 --> 00:44:44,916
Here's the thing, dude.

826
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:48,083
Go out into the streets
and cause some terror.

827
00:44:48,166 --> 00:44:51,416
-Make it happen. No questions asked.
-Kill them all. Make an example.

828
00:44:51,500 --> 00:44:53,750
-It's war. It's war now.
-Do not hesitate.

829
00:44:53,833 --> 00:44:55,958
-Mess with us, it's war.
-Make it happen.

830
00:45:00,541 --> 00:45:02,666
This is our time!

831
00:45:02,750 --> 00:45:05,250
Make it work. They come here to test us?

832
00:45:05,333 --> 00:45:07,500
That shit don't fly around here.
You heard me?

833
00:45:07,583 --> 00:45:09,708
No one's giving the brothers
a dirty look today.

834
00:45:09,791 --> 00:45:11,708
Things are gonna blow up everywhere.

835
00:45:11,791 --> 00:45:13,000
We're the Brotherhood.

836
00:45:14,208 --> 00:45:16,750
If they want war,
then that's what they're gonna get.

837
00:45:16,833 --> 00:45:18,500
They're gonna learn the hard way.

838
00:45:18,583 --> 00:45:21,291
They don't respect us,
so now they're paying the price.

839
00:45:21,375 --> 00:45:24,166
They need to know we make the rules here.

840
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:28,833
You know what to do.

841
00:45:29,541 --> 00:45:31,666
Come on, brothers. The call is out.

842
00:45:38,208 --> 00:45:41,458
-Let's show them!
-The system is going down!

843
00:45:41,541 --> 00:45:44,250
-This is war!
-It's the Brotherhood!

844
00:45:45,458 --> 00:45:47,416
We are the Brotherhood!

845
00:45:47,500 --> 00:45:50,250
-Come on! Let's do it!
-Come on! Let's go!

846
00:45:50,875 --> 00:45:53,958
The riots that have been
taking place in the prisons of São Paulo

847
00:45:54,041 --> 00:45:55,291
since early this morning

848
00:45:55,375 --> 00:45:58,791
are in retaliation for the transfer
of a number of Brotherhood members

849
00:45:58,875 --> 00:46:00,875
to the maximum security RDD unit.

850
00:46:00,958 --> 00:46:04,416
That now, ten years after
the death of their leader, Edson Ferreira,

851
00:46:04,500 --> 00:46:05,916
known as Edinho "Savage,"

852
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:09,333
the Brotherhood has cemented
its reputation for organized violence,

853
00:46:09,416 --> 00:46:11,333
claiming responsibility for the riots.

854
00:46:11,416 --> 00:46:12,250
There are 25…

855
00:46:12,333 --> 00:46:16,083
No, now it's up to 29 prisons
where rioting has been reported.

856
00:46:16,166 --> 00:46:20,000
The riots have spread rapidly
throughout multiple regions of the state.

857
00:46:20,083 --> 00:46:23,625
This escalation is marked
by unprecedented coordination.

858
00:46:23,708 --> 00:46:26,375
And public safety experts
have been warning

859
00:46:26,458 --> 00:46:31,000
about this capacity for mobilization
for quite some time now.

860
00:46:35,750 --> 00:46:38,708
Hey, buddy. Give me a latte, would you?

861
00:46:46,125 --> 00:46:50,458
…the number of casualties
continue to increase by the hour.

862
00:46:50,541 --> 00:46:52,375
As of now, we have noticed

863
00:46:52,458 --> 00:46:55,875
that the prison riots
show no signs of stopping.

864
00:46:55,958 --> 00:46:57,041
Uncontained.

865
00:46:57,125 --> 00:47:00,708
Ten prisoners, two in Taubaté,
and eight in São Sebastião,

866
00:47:00,791 --> 00:47:05,083
have died from burns sustained
after setting fire to their cells.

867
00:47:05,583 --> 00:47:07,458
The Counselor, in the flesh.

868
00:47:08,916 --> 00:47:10,000
It's an honor.

869
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:12,083
Where is she?

870
00:47:15,208 --> 00:47:16,458
Are you alone?

871
00:47:17,750 --> 00:47:18,916
I gave you my word, right?

872
00:47:19,875 --> 00:47:23,500
Even though this meeting is
in front of a police station, I'm here.

873
00:47:23,583 --> 00:47:26,166
You didn't really have
much of a choice about that.

874
00:47:27,416 --> 00:47:30,333
With the rest of your pack in the zoo
making such a mess of things.

875
00:47:31,291 --> 00:47:35,333
Where is she? Locked up at the station?
Or am I here just to be intimidated?

876
00:47:35,416 --> 00:47:36,750
Relax.

877
00:47:39,125 --> 00:47:41,166
The baby savage is fine.

878
00:47:43,333 --> 00:47:46,750
First, you need to tell me
where my money is.

879
00:47:54,958 --> 00:47:57,000
I wanna see if she's okay first.

880
00:47:59,708 --> 00:48:02,291
What's that saying
you gangsters keep repeating?

881
00:48:02,375 --> 00:48:03,541
Um…

882
00:48:03,625 --> 00:48:05,250
"What's right is right."

883
00:48:06,250 --> 00:48:07,375
Isn't that it?

884
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:40,208
Wait.

885
00:50:10,791 --> 00:50:12,750
What the fuck is this?

886
00:50:12,833 --> 00:50:16,000
-Elisa! Elisa!
-Requesting backup! Requesting backup!

887
00:50:16,083 --> 00:50:17,333
Get back here, dammit!

888
00:50:18,708 --> 00:50:19,666
Cris!

889
00:50:21,458 --> 00:50:23,333
-What was that?
-Get down! Get down!

890
00:50:27,250 --> 00:50:29,750
What's going on? See anything?

891
00:50:29,833 --> 00:50:33,041
-Elisa! Elisa!
-Take her! Go! Now!

892
00:50:37,291 --> 00:50:39,458
This is the fucking Brotherhood!

893
00:50:39,541 --> 00:50:41,000
Get down! Get down!

894
00:50:41,083 --> 00:50:43,125
Hey, hey, hey! Come here!

895
00:50:45,666 --> 00:50:48,041
Go, kid! Go make a name for yourself!

896
00:50:50,416 --> 00:50:52,208
Come on! Let's go! Let's go!

897
00:50:52,291 --> 00:50:53,958
Get out of the way! Go!

898
00:50:54,041 --> 00:50:56,625
Here you go,
you sons of bitches! Take this!

899
00:50:59,666 --> 00:51:01,833
Take this you fucking pigs!

900
00:51:10,083 --> 00:51:11,458
Go! Go, go, go, go!

901
00:51:11,541 --> 00:51:13,250
Motherfucker, go!

902
00:51:14,916 --> 00:51:17,291
Motherfucker! You fucking deserve it!

903
00:51:24,666 --> 00:51:28,500
-Fucking bitch! You set me up, didn't you?
-I don't know anything about this!

904
00:51:40,166 --> 00:51:41,541
Cris!

905
00:51:41,625 --> 00:51:43,416
Elisa!

906
00:51:43,958 --> 00:51:45,083
Elisa!

907
00:51:45,833 --> 00:51:47,666
-Cris!
-Elisa!

908
00:51:47,750 --> 00:51:49,000
Cris!

909
00:51:50,125 --> 00:51:51,291
Elisa!

910
00:51:51,375 --> 00:51:53,208
-Cris!
-Elisa!

911
00:51:55,291 --> 00:51:56,625
-Get me out of here!
-Elisa!

912
00:51:56,708 --> 00:51:58,750
-Get me out of here!
-Elisa! No!

913
00:51:58,833 --> 00:52:00,875
-Cris!
-No!

914
00:52:17,958 --> 00:52:21,291
Sir, is it possible to tell me
the account holder's ID number, please?

915
00:52:21,375 --> 00:52:23,541
But I've given you
my ID number three times.

916
00:52:23,625 --> 00:52:27,541
My problem isn't that hard to solve.
I just need you to check if--

917
00:52:27,625 --> 00:52:29,916
My God. What was that?

918
00:52:32,208 --> 00:52:35,583
São Paulo police are currently
being held hostage by the criminals.

919
00:52:35,666 --> 00:52:40,208
The city now faces a day of chaos
with attacks happening in several regions.

920
00:52:40,291 --> 00:52:43,458
Guys, look, isn't that the station
just down the street?

921
00:52:43,541 --> 00:52:47,291
…was shot at about half an hour ago.
The atmosphere is one of tension and fear.

922
00:52:47,375 --> 00:52:50,625
Everyone. Over here, please.
I need everybody's attention for a minute.

923
00:52:50,708 --> 00:52:52,625
Look, because of the situation
on the streets,

924
00:52:52,708 --> 00:52:54,375
I'm gonna let everyone go home, okay?

925
00:52:54,458 --> 00:52:57,166
But don't panic. Just get your bags
and your stuff and let's go.

926
00:52:57,250 --> 00:53:00,041
I'll try to take the subway.

927
00:53:00,125 --> 00:53:02,166
-It's a nightmare.
-Are you getting reception?

928
00:53:05,833 --> 00:53:08,416
Hello? I'm on my way now.
Stay there. Don't go anywhere.

929
00:53:08,500 --> 00:53:09,791
Don't leave the house.

930
00:53:10,541 --> 00:53:11,750
Move it, Grandma!

931
00:53:11,833 --> 00:53:13,708
Somebody needs to be
home when they get there.

932
00:53:16,250 --> 00:53:19,666
Incinerated buses,
banks, and security forces under fire.

933
00:53:19,750 --> 00:53:21,875
Watch out! Come on! Move it!

934
00:53:45,541 --> 00:53:47,416
It's a war. There's shooting happening.

935
00:53:47,500 --> 00:53:50,708
The kids are in school!
I have to pick up my son!

936
00:53:50,791 --> 00:53:53,791
-Get out of the way!
-Stay there! I'll be there soon!

937
00:53:53,875 --> 00:53:55,208
Stay there. Don't move.

938
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:09,458
Give him some cover, man.

939
00:54:15,250 --> 00:54:17,375
It'll be smooth as silk.
Just gimme a minute.

940
00:54:17,875 --> 00:54:19,000
What's going on?

941
00:54:26,791 --> 00:54:29,041
Here. It's an open line.

942
00:54:29,875 --> 00:54:33,041
Hey, bro,
I've seen guys hide shit up their asses,

943
00:54:33,125 --> 00:54:34,958
but in their fat rolls,
it's the first time.

944
00:54:35,041 --> 00:54:37,250
Watch it, dude. Come on.

945
00:54:39,541 --> 00:54:41,583
I wonder what else he's got in there.

946
00:54:54,083 --> 00:54:56,458
-Hello.
-It's me. I'll be quick.

947
00:54:57,041 --> 00:54:58,958
I need you in the negotiation.

948
00:54:59,708 --> 00:55:01,333
Go back and talk to the secretary.

949
00:55:01,416 --> 00:55:03,166
You need to tell him
that the price of peace

950
00:55:03,250 --> 00:55:04,583
is for them to drop the transfer.

951
00:55:04,666 --> 00:55:06,375
Negotiate with what?

952
00:55:07,000 --> 00:55:09,500
Do you really think
that with all these riots going on,

953
00:55:09,583 --> 00:55:13,041
with this many cops getting killed,
that they're gonna revoke the transfer?

954
00:55:13,125 --> 00:55:14,333
The press is all over it.

955
00:55:14,416 --> 00:55:15,375
That's the point.

956
00:55:15,458 --> 00:55:18,875
If they don't agree to it, we keep up
the attack until they fucking surrender.

957
00:55:18,958 --> 00:55:22,000
This shit has kept me
from paying the ransom for Elisa.

958
00:55:22,083 --> 00:55:23,958
She should be home by now, dammit!

959
00:55:24,041 --> 00:55:26,625
We'll send someone to find her
while you take care of this.

960
00:55:26,708 --> 00:55:28,625
Who knows if she's alive, Ivan?

961
00:55:29,166 --> 00:55:31,750
There are people dying
right now as we speak.

962
00:55:33,791 --> 00:55:37,041
I need you to trust me.
The governor will give in.

963
00:55:37,541 --> 00:55:39,291
Now tell me.
I need to know if you're gonna--

964
00:55:39,375 --> 00:55:41,541
What I'm saying is that
I'll never forgive you

965
00:55:41,625 --> 00:55:42,833
if something happens to her.

966
00:55:43,958 --> 00:55:47,291
Dammit, Christina, listen for once!
I'm running out of time.

967
00:55:47,375 --> 00:55:49,625
Just do your job.
Set up a meeting with him.

968
00:55:49,708 --> 00:55:51,375
Negotiate this fucking transfer.

969
00:55:52,791 --> 00:55:54,500
Now you wanna negotiate?

970
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:56,250
Why don't you send Minor?

971
00:55:56,333 --> 00:55:58,541
Come on. Hide that phone, Ivan.

972
00:55:58,625 --> 00:56:00,041
What's it gonna be, Cris?

973
00:56:00,833 --> 00:56:02,875
Am I gonna be left to rot in solitary?

974
00:56:03,375 --> 00:56:05,875
I won't even be able
to see you during visitation.

975
00:56:05,958 --> 00:56:07,583
Is that what you want for us?

976
00:56:07,666 --> 00:56:10,000
We're fucking there.

977
00:56:10,083 --> 00:56:12,458
Make room for fresh meat.
The big boss is here.

978
00:56:13,041 --> 00:56:14,000
Cristina.

979
00:56:15,541 --> 00:56:17,375
You know there's no going back, right?

980
00:56:17,458 --> 00:56:18,625
Ivan.

981
00:56:18,708 --> 00:56:21,875
Big boss my ass.
That son of a bitch's reign is over.

982
00:56:21,958 --> 00:56:23,791
-That's for sure.
-Cristina.

983
00:56:24,791 --> 00:56:26,833
-Come on. Hide that phone!
-Cris.

984
00:56:26,916 --> 00:56:28,625
-Do it now!
-Cristina.

985
00:56:59,083 --> 00:57:02,375
While the population
hides behind locked doors,

986
00:57:02,458 --> 00:57:05,000
criminals act with military boldness.

987
00:57:05,083 --> 00:57:08,625
Organized crime has declared war
against the state.

988
00:57:08,708 --> 00:57:13,791
Chaos has taken over the streets
and fear has spread like wildfire.

989
00:57:13,875 --> 00:57:15,708
The city that never sleeps…

990
00:57:15,791 --> 00:57:18,500
…is now living a waking nightmare.

991
00:57:21,083 --> 00:57:23,458
Hey, Sarge. Where the fuck are you?

992
00:57:23,541 --> 00:57:26,583
Tell me where you are, man.
I'm worried about you.

993
00:57:27,083 --> 00:57:29,541
Did those motherfuckers
do anything to you, Anselmo?

994
00:57:30,041 --> 00:57:32,875
Listen, I still have the package here,
but I can't keep her much longer.

995
00:57:32,958 --> 00:57:34,958
I need you to tell me what to do.

996
00:57:35,458 --> 00:57:37,083
Don't leave me alone. Call me.

997
00:57:39,833 --> 00:57:42,250
Could I have some water?

998
00:57:52,625 --> 00:57:53,625
Hmm.

999
00:58:06,958 --> 00:58:09,875
Don't you think it's weird
he's not answering and he left you alone?

1000
00:58:09,958 --> 00:58:12,666
Shut up. Nobody asked you anything.

1001
00:58:18,375 --> 00:58:21,208
Well, it looks like he knew
the plan wouldn't work and he split.

1002
00:58:21,291 --> 00:58:22,958
He'll lay all the blame on you.

1003
00:58:25,416 --> 00:58:27,541
It's obvious you don't have
anything to do with this.

1004
00:58:27,625 --> 00:58:28,791
There's still time to fix it.

1005
00:58:28,875 --> 00:58:31,333
-You just have to let me go--
-Shut up! Shut the fuck up!

1006
00:58:32,708 --> 00:58:34,500
What do you think, that I'm stupid?

1007
00:58:35,333 --> 00:58:36,791
Do I look like an idiot?

1008
00:58:38,083 --> 00:58:40,583
Let you go.
No one's letting you go, dammit.

1009
00:58:41,083 --> 00:58:44,125
I'll only let you leave
when the fucking phone rings.

1010
00:58:44,708 --> 00:58:47,666
And you better hope… no, pray…

1011
00:58:48,375 --> 00:58:50,708
pray that nothing happened
to any of my partners.

1012
00:58:50,791 --> 00:58:53,291
'Cause if something happened,
you're gonna pay for it.

1013
00:58:58,958 --> 00:59:01,041
Wait, I also don't agree
with what the radio says

1014
00:59:01,125 --> 00:59:02,541
the Brotherhood is doing.

1015
00:59:02,625 --> 00:59:04,625
You don't agree, my ass, girl.

1016
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:07,250
The fuck you don't.

1017
00:59:08,500 --> 00:59:10,125
You hate the police.

1018
00:59:12,083 --> 00:59:14,625
And I don't just mean thugs.
I mean everyone.

1019
00:59:16,166 --> 00:59:18,875
There's always someone like you
clapping and shouting,

1020
00:59:18,958 --> 00:59:21,500
lighting fireworks when one of us falls.

1021
00:59:24,666 --> 00:59:25,916
It's not hate.

1022
00:59:26,750 --> 00:59:27,916
It's fear.

1023
00:59:30,375 --> 00:59:32,500
We've always been more scared of you
than the criminals.

1024
00:59:32,583 --> 00:59:34,375
Ask anyone, they'll tell you the same.

1025
00:59:36,500 --> 00:59:37,583
The police

1026
00:59:38,083 --> 00:59:40,041
are out there to protect good people,

1027
00:59:40,541 --> 00:59:42,666
risking their lives and earning peanuts.

1028
00:59:43,250 --> 00:59:44,916
Now, as for the thugs,

1029
00:59:46,083 --> 00:59:47,541
with thugs, little girl,

1030
00:59:48,500 --> 00:59:50,291
we have to come down hard.

1031
00:59:51,458 --> 00:59:53,708
Or do you think
there's other ways to get justice?

1032
00:59:58,375 --> 01:00:00,625
Depends on what you think justice is.

1033
01:00:02,000 --> 01:00:03,791
Is this justice? Hmm?

1034
01:00:07,791 --> 01:00:09,291
That's all I needed.

1035
01:00:12,291 --> 01:00:14,583
Getting a fucking lecture from a thug.

1036
01:00:17,791 --> 01:00:19,708
Is that why you joined the police?

1037
01:00:20,875 --> 01:00:22,208
You're a coward.

1038
01:00:24,666 --> 01:00:26,000
Shut up!

1039
01:00:36,041 --> 01:00:38,333
The city is now officially in lockdown,

1040
01:00:38,416 --> 01:00:40,666
and public transportation
has been suspended.

1041
01:00:40,750 --> 01:00:42,833
Stores and banks are closed.

1042
01:00:43,333 --> 01:00:46,083
Classes have been suspended in schools.

1043
01:00:46,166 --> 01:00:50,000
Furthermore, the rebellions
inside the prisons continue to escalate…

1044
01:00:50,791 --> 01:00:51,875
Here's the address.

1045
01:00:51,958 --> 01:00:55,125
Shoot to kill, got it?
Remember, every cop has a gun at home.

1046
01:00:55,625 --> 01:00:57,708
-Don't screw this up, guys.
-All right, let's go.

1047
01:00:57,791 --> 01:00:59,791
-Let's go, brothers.
-Get outta here.

1048
01:00:59,875 --> 01:01:01,708
-Stay sharp. Let's go.
-Hey, Counselor.

1049
01:01:01,791 --> 01:01:04,041
-Justice. Let's move.
-Let's get this done.

1050
01:01:05,666 --> 01:01:07,041
Let's go. Come on.

1051
01:01:09,875 --> 01:01:12,000
Hey, Rui. I need your help with something.

1052
01:01:14,791 --> 01:01:17,333
You know I have
the utmost respect for you, right?

1053
01:01:18,125 --> 01:01:19,166
What is it?

1054
01:01:21,208 --> 01:01:24,708
Look, Counselor, I'm fully aware
that this family would never be what it is

1055
01:01:24,791 --> 01:01:26,125
if it weren't for your work.

1056
01:01:26,625 --> 01:01:29,833
But I just got orders from above
not to cooperate with you anymore.

1057
01:01:29,916 --> 01:01:31,500
Listen to me.

1058
01:01:32,250 --> 01:01:34,416
I got you into this family.

1059
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:38,541
I'm responsible for your success.
You know I've always done the right thing.

1060
01:01:39,166 --> 01:01:40,166
I know that.

1061
01:01:40,708 --> 01:01:42,416
-But I got orders--
-But nothing.

1062
01:01:42,500 --> 01:01:44,583
The fucking pigs have my niece, dammit.

1063
01:01:44,666 --> 01:01:46,208
Her life is in danger.

1064
01:01:46,750 --> 01:01:48,166
So fuck Ivan.

1065
01:01:52,375 --> 01:01:53,500
Tell me what you need.

1066
01:01:57,458 --> 01:02:00,250
I just need you to get
the address of the pig who's got her.

1067
01:02:03,791 --> 01:02:05,291
Civil police?

1068
01:02:05,375 --> 01:02:06,375
Military.

1069
01:02:06,958 --> 01:02:09,083
If you know the area where he operates in…

1070
01:02:09,833 --> 01:02:11,250
60th Battalion.

1071
01:02:11,333 --> 01:02:13,833
The bastard didn't even bother to hide it.

1072
01:02:15,958 --> 01:02:17,416
I know his face. Pull it up.

1073
01:02:19,083 --> 01:02:20,708
Okay, I'll see what I can do.

1074
01:02:25,166 --> 01:02:26,750
-Son of a bitch.
-Is that him?

1075
01:02:27,708 --> 01:02:30,000
No, that one's gone. Keep going.

1076
01:02:38,416 --> 01:02:39,666
Here!

1077
01:02:41,166 --> 01:02:42,916
"André Luis Borges."

1078
01:02:45,041 --> 01:02:45,958
Got him.

1079
01:02:52,791 --> 01:02:55,791
Stores closed early,
classes were suspended,

1080
01:02:55,875 --> 01:02:58,208
and several bus lines are not running.

1081
01:02:58,291 --> 01:03:01,875
São Paulo faces a wave
of coordinated attacks by the Brotherhood.

1082
01:03:01,958 --> 01:03:04,416
The organization
has attacked several targets,

1083
01:03:04,500 --> 01:03:06,500
showing strength inside
and outside the prisons.

1084
01:03:06,583 --> 01:03:08,208
In the midst of the crossfire,

1085
01:03:08,291 --> 01:03:10,583
a curfew has been imposed in the capital.

1086
01:03:10,666 --> 01:03:14,250
It's not even 6:00 p.m.
and the largest city in the country

1087
01:03:14,333 --> 01:03:15,875
is now a ghost town.

1088
01:03:57,875 --> 01:04:01,750
I go down this street every day.
Today, it feels like a different city.

1089
01:04:01,833 --> 01:04:03,958
I've never seen anything like this.

1090
01:04:04,041 --> 01:04:06,625
They sent everyone home.
How am I supposed to get home?

1091
01:04:06,708 --> 01:04:08,750
I waited two hours for the bus.

1092
01:04:14,166 --> 01:04:15,541
Hands on your head!

1093
01:04:15,625 --> 01:04:17,791
-Everyone against the wall!
-You, in the middle.

1094
01:04:17,875 --> 01:04:20,000
-Everyone against the fucking wall!
-Come on!

1095
01:04:20,083 --> 01:04:22,583
-Go, go, go, go!
-Please, sir. I'm a working man.

1096
01:04:22,666 --> 01:04:24,333
-I just came--
-Who the fuck asked you?

1097
01:04:24,416 --> 01:04:27,375
You only speak when I tell you. Got it?
Anyone here got a record?

1098
01:04:29,458 --> 01:04:31,791
Do you guys speak my language or not?

1099
01:04:31,875 --> 01:04:33,666
Does anyone here have a record?

1100
01:04:34,333 --> 01:04:35,541
Here, Captain.

1101
01:04:36,041 --> 01:04:37,041
Turn around, dammit!

1102
01:04:37,541 --> 01:04:38,916
This one's a convict.

1103
01:04:39,833 --> 01:04:41,375
A Christian with tattoos?

1104
01:04:41,875 --> 01:04:44,583
-You got a record, right, man?
-I'm a working man, sir.

1105
01:04:45,750 --> 01:04:46,708
Hey, ma'am.

1106
01:04:47,208 --> 01:04:49,375
What the hell are you doing
out of your house, ma'am?

1107
01:04:51,291 --> 01:04:52,666
Get over there!

1108
01:04:52,750 --> 01:04:53,708
Go on, now!

1109
01:04:54,291 --> 01:04:57,000
-I've already served my time.
-Who fucking cares?

1110
01:04:58,250 --> 01:05:00,666
You mess with the cops,
you die, motherfucker.

1111
01:05:42,833 --> 01:05:43,833
Son!

1112
01:05:49,625 --> 01:05:50,458
Son!

1113
01:05:55,416 --> 01:05:56,375
Son!

1114
01:06:01,833 --> 01:06:03,125
My son.

1115
01:06:04,916 --> 01:06:06,041
André.

1116
01:06:15,500 --> 01:06:17,208
-André.
-Hey, Mom.

1117
01:06:17,291 --> 01:06:19,291
Oh, my son.

1118
01:06:19,375 --> 01:06:21,166
-Thank God you're okay.
-Mm…

1119
01:06:24,041 --> 01:06:25,416
Blessed be His name.

1120
01:06:25,916 --> 01:06:28,708
How come you're home so early?
Weren't you going to church?

1121
01:06:29,208 --> 01:06:31,500
People all over the city
are just getting murdered.

1122
01:06:31,583 --> 01:06:32,458
It's like a war.

1123
01:06:32,541 --> 01:06:35,166
You wouldn't believe
what I went through to get here, son.

1124
01:06:35,666 --> 01:06:37,791
-But are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

1125
01:06:37,875 --> 01:06:39,708
But I was worried sick.

1126
01:06:40,208 --> 01:06:43,000
What happened to your car?
Did someone shoot at you?

1127
01:06:43,083 --> 01:06:46,333
Long story, Mom.
You know I can take care of myself, right?

1128
01:06:47,500 --> 01:06:50,708
If I ever lose you, my son,
I'll ask God to take me too.

1129
01:06:50,791 --> 01:06:52,458
Don't even think that, Mom.

1130
01:06:53,166 --> 01:06:55,416
I prayed so much
for you to be a police officer.

1131
01:06:55,500 --> 01:06:57,583
But I don't know if I did the right thing.

1132
01:06:58,083 --> 01:07:02,583
There's so much evil in the world,
sometimes I think hell is right here.

1133
01:07:03,166 --> 01:07:04,958
Well, I think I need a shower.

1134
01:07:05,041 --> 01:07:06,375
No! Hey!

1135
01:07:06,875 --> 01:07:08,875
Uh, Mom, I…

1136
01:07:10,416 --> 01:07:12,375
I only had breakfast today.

1137
01:07:12,458 --> 01:07:14,916
I had a shitty day.

1138
01:07:15,541 --> 01:07:18,208
And the only thing that got me through it

1139
01:07:18,291 --> 01:07:21,500
was knowing that, when I got home,
I would get to eat Mrs. Ângela's food.

1140
01:07:21,583 --> 01:07:23,375
Oh, sweetie.

1141
01:07:24,458 --> 01:07:26,541
I was wondering if you could
make us some french fries.

1142
01:07:27,125 --> 01:07:29,666
Oh, sweetie, what I wouldn't do for you.

1143
01:07:29,750 --> 01:07:31,375
My God.

1144
01:07:34,083 --> 01:07:35,750
Fries, sweetie?

1145
01:07:35,833 --> 01:07:37,666
-Yeah.
-Okay.

1146
01:07:57,708 --> 01:08:00,041
Answer, motherfucker.

1147
01:08:04,833 --> 01:08:07,416
Anselmo, where the fuck are you?

1148
01:08:07,500 --> 01:08:10,000
They're killing everyone,
and I'm alone with the girl.

1149
01:08:10,083 --> 01:08:13,125
I don't know what to do with her anymore.
I'm doing this for you, man.

1150
01:08:13,666 --> 01:08:15,958
Did they do anything to you?
Answer the fucking--

1151
01:08:16,041 --> 01:08:17,125
Fuck!

1152
01:08:18,375 --> 01:08:19,541
Fuck, man!

1153
01:09:14,541 --> 01:09:15,875
Get me out of here.

1154
01:09:16,375 --> 01:09:18,166
-What's going--
-Be quiet. Be quiet, dammit.

1155
01:09:18,250 --> 01:09:19,208
No.

1156
01:09:21,250 --> 01:09:22,208
Shut up.

1157
01:09:23,458 --> 01:09:25,416
Shut up. Shut the fuck up.

1158
01:09:28,750 --> 01:09:29,833
Shut up.

1159
01:09:32,166 --> 01:09:33,458
Quiet, dammit!

1160
01:09:34,708 --> 01:09:36,666
Shut up.

1161
01:09:37,833 --> 01:09:39,375
Shut up.

1162
01:09:46,750 --> 01:09:47,583
Shut up!

1163
01:10:38,666 --> 01:10:41,708
For God's sake! What's going on here?

1164
01:10:43,166 --> 01:10:45,208
Are you okay, dear?

1165
01:10:46,916 --> 01:10:49,458
Please tell me you are okay.

1166
01:10:49,541 --> 01:10:51,875
For the love of God! What's going on here?

1167
01:10:51,958 --> 01:10:53,625
Who is this girl?

1168
01:10:53,708 --> 01:10:56,375
What were you doing to her, André Luis?

1169
01:10:56,458 --> 01:10:58,083
-Tell me!
-Calm down.

1170
01:10:59,375 --> 01:11:00,791
I can explain, Mom.

1171
01:11:57,125 --> 01:12:00,000
André Luis, please,
just tell me what's happening.

1172
01:12:00,083 --> 01:12:02,916
What's happening, Mom,
is that all these men are out there.

1173
01:12:03,416 --> 01:12:06,166
There was a major issue at work
so I had to bring this shit home.

1174
01:12:06,250 --> 01:12:09,500
Now you do your thing.
Don't bother me. Don't meddle!

1175
01:12:11,125 --> 01:12:14,166
This was that partner of yours,
wasn't it, André Luis?

1176
01:12:14,250 --> 01:12:16,958
I told you that man is not your friend!

1177
01:12:17,458 --> 01:12:20,083
Of course he's my friend, Mom.
I'm his son's godfather.

1178
01:12:20,583 --> 01:12:22,666
But he's not a good person.

1179
01:12:23,416 --> 01:12:26,083
I know you'd never do
something like that alone.

1180
01:12:26,166 --> 01:12:28,458
What do you mean, Mom? Just look around.

1181
01:12:28,541 --> 01:12:32,583
They're all bad people, all thugs!
Look what they're doing to the city!

1182
01:12:33,083 --> 01:12:36,208
Oh, so now you're God?
Dealing out justice?

1183
01:12:36,291 --> 01:12:39,583
Stop it, André Luis.
That's not how I raised you.

1184
01:12:39,666 --> 01:12:41,250
Are you listening to me?

1185
01:12:41,333 --> 01:12:44,208
Look, you just stay here,
and I'm gonna go solve this problem.

1186
01:12:45,500 --> 01:12:47,708
You can't just leave her anywhere.

1187
01:12:48,375 --> 01:12:51,375
You worry too much, Mom.
You're gonna get me in trouble.

1188
01:12:51,458 --> 01:12:55,708
I'm going to get you in trouble?
Look what you've brought into our house!

1189
01:13:01,916 --> 01:13:03,458
What's that? What's that money, Mom?

1190
01:13:03,541 --> 01:13:05,333
It's the emergency money I saved.

1191
01:13:05,416 --> 01:13:06,625
You're a good boy, son.

1192
01:13:06,708 --> 01:13:08,458
I'm not going to let you ruin your life

1193
01:13:08,541 --> 01:13:12,041
over something you did
in the heat of the moment, André Luis.

1194
01:13:13,916 --> 01:13:16,125
It's decided, son. Go on!

1195
01:13:22,333 --> 01:13:24,125
Go get the girl upstairs.

1196
01:13:53,208 --> 01:13:54,500
Elisa! Elisa!

1197
01:13:54,583 --> 01:13:55,541
-Cris!
-Elisa!

1198
01:13:55,625 --> 01:13:57,166
-Help me. I want to get out.
-Thank God.

1199
01:13:57,250 --> 01:13:59,166
-Get me out. I'm tied up.
-I'll help you out.

1200
01:14:04,916 --> 01:14:06,625
-I'll get you out of here.
-Uh-huh.

1201
01:14:06,708 --> 01:14:07,625
Calm down.

1202
01:14:08,916 --> 01:14:10,750
Take it. C'mon, c'mon, c'mon.

1203
01:14:15,583 --> 01:14:16,958
Let's go. Get up.

1204
01:14:24,666 --> 01:14:26,333
What are you gonna do to me?

1205
01:14:26,416 --> 01:14:28,500
-Shut up.
-Let me go, for God's sake.

1206
01:14:28,583 --> 01:14:30,083
Shut up and get down there.

1207
01:14:35,208 --> 01:14:36,333
Stay there.

1208
01:14:41,583 --> 01:14:42,750
Calm down.

1209
01:14:43,500 --> 01:14:45,083
Be fucking quiet.

1210
01:14:45,166 --> 01:14:48,416
Calm down. There's still time
to get the money you want. Listen to me.

1211
01:14:48,500 --> 01:14:50,000
Shut up!

1212
01:15:23,833 --> 01:15:27,166
Nightly News is brought to you by Fresh.

1213
01:15:27,250 --> 01:15:28,625
Daily relief.

1214
01:15:28,708 --> 01:15:32,166
Fresh breath, guaranteed confidence.

1215
01:18:08,583 --> 01:18:10,875
Mom, what are you doing?
Don't take her hood off.

1216
01:18:10,958 --> 01:18:12,416
We're far from home.

1217
01:18:13,000 --> 01:18:14,083
Where are we going?

1218
01:18:14,833 --> 01:18:17,166
Calm down. Everything will be fine.

1219
01:18:25,125 --> 01:18:27,958
For God's sake. Where are you taking me?

1220
01:18:28,041 --> 01:18:31,750
You should thank God every day
that my mother crossed your path.

1221
01:18:31,833 --> 01:18:33,083
Hear me, pretty girl?

1222
01:18:46,208 --> 01:18:48,750
You have ten new voicemails.

1223
01:18:48,833 --> 01:18:51,541
To listen to your messages, press one.

1224
01:18:54,416 --> 01:18:57,500
Dude, where are you? I keep calling
and you're not answering, dammit.

1225
01:18:57,583 --> 01:18:58,625
I'm worried.

1226
01:18:59,291 --> 01:19:00,875
Did you hear about Anselmo?

1227
01:19:02,041 --> 01:19:04,583
Those Brotherhood motherfuckers
killed him.

1228
01:19:05,791 --> 01:19:08,833
His wife just got here.
I didn't know what to say.

1229
01:19:10,208 --> 01:19:11,958
They shot him in the face.

1230
01:19:12,958 --> 01:19:15,333
Call me, brother.
I hope you get this message.

1231
01:19:44,125 --> 01:19:44,958
Get out.

1232
01:19:47,708 --> 01:19:49,333
Come on. Are you deaf? Get out.

1233
01:19:50,375 --> 01:19:51,541
